<figureCitation box="[378,475,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[205,1376,707,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-204@12.[199,1388,705,1912]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Eccoptolonthus fuyuensis Fei &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. A. Habitus; B. aedeagus, dorsal (parameral side) view; C. aedeagus, lateral view; D. sternite IX of male; E. tergite X of male; F. sternite VIII of male; g. stylus of tergite IX of male. Scale bars, A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H= 0.2 mm;" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4640491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4640491/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Figs. 7E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[487,524,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1916,1940]" captionTargetBox="[270,1307,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[265,1323,181,1892]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Eccoptolonthus fuyuensis Fei &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. A. aedeagus, dorsal (parameral side) view; B. aedeagus, lateral view; C. sternite IX of male; D. tergite X of male; E. sternite VIII of male; F. stylus of tergite IX of male. Scale bars, A, B= 0.1 mm; C, D= 0.13 mm; E, F= 0.18 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4640495" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4640495/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">8D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,1545]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">
Aedeagus in ventral view with median lobe almost as wide as paramere, slightly expanded in the middle and narrowed into truncate apex, middle part of paramere narrowed, apex of paramere approximately circular, with dense peg setae irregularly arranged along apical portion of paramere (
<figureCitation box="[942,1040,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[205,1376,707,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-204@12.[199,1388,705,1912]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Eccoptolonthus fuyuensis Fei &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. A. Habitus; B. aedeagus, dorsal (parameral side) view; C. aedeagus, lateral view; D. sternite IX of male; E. tergite X of male; F. sternite VIII of male; g. stylus of tergite IX of male. Scale bars, A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H= 0.2 mm;" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4640491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4640491/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Figs. 7B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1051,1089,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1916,1940]" captionTargetBox="[270,1307,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[265,1323,181,1892]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Eccoptolonthus fuyuensis Fei &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. A. aedeagus, dorsal (parameral side) view; B. aedeagus, lateral view; C. sternite IX of male; D. tergite X of male; E. sternite VIII of male; F. stylus of tergite IX of male. Scale bars, A, B= 0.1 mm; C, D= 0.13 mm; E, F= 0.18 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4640495" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4640495/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">8A</figureCitation>
); in lateral view, apical portion moderately bent ventrally, paramere elongate, apical-half of paramere ellipsoidal, some fine setae on apex. (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1432,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[205,1376,707,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-204@12.[199,1388,705,1912]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Eccoptolonthus fuyuensis Fei &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. A. Habitus; B. aedeagus, dorsal (parameral side) view; C. aedeagus, lateral view; D. sternite IX of male; E. tergite X of male; F. sternite VIII of male; g. stylus of tergite IX of male. Scale bars, A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H= 0.2 mm;" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4640491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4640491/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Figs.7C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,187,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1916,1940]" captionTargetBox="[270,1307,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[265,1323,181,1892]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Eccoptolonthus fuyuensis Fei &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. A. aedeagus, dorsal (parameral side) view; B. aedeagus, lateral view; C. sternite IX of male; D. tergite X of male; E. sternite VIII of male; F. stylus of tergite IX of male. Scale bars, A, B= 0.1 mm; C, D= 0.13 mm; E, F= 0.18 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4640495" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4640495/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">8B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="487" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,1545]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1159,1185]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Fei &amp; Zhou" authorityName="Fei &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2021" box="[321,740,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eccoptolonthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuyuensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[321,605,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Eccoptolonthus fuyuensis</emphasis>
Fei &amp; Zhou
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[746,834,1159,1185]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[746,834,1159,1185]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sharp, 1874)" authorityName="Schillhammer" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1874" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eccoptolonthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutiliventris">
<emphasis box="[1036,1348,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Eccoptolonthus rutiliventris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sharp, D." pageId="14" pageNumber="487" pagination="47 - 48" refId="ref16531" refString="Sharp, D. (1874) The Staphylinidae of Japan. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1, 47 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1874. tb 00159. x" type="journal article" year="1874">Sharp, 1874</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
but can be easily distinguished by the sensory peg setae of paramere uniformly distributed at the apex of paramere; in lateral view, the length of sensory peg setae about 0.25 times as long as width of the paramere (obviously shorter in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sharp, 1874))" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[263,740,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eccoptolonthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutilivenris">
<emphasis box="[263,568,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Eccoptolonthus rutilivenris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sharp, D." box="[582,721,1267,1293]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" pagination="47 - 48" refId="ref16531" refString="Sharp, D. (1874) The Staphylinidae of Japan. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1, 47 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1874. tb 00159. x" type="journal article" year="1874">Sharp, 1874</bibRefCitation>
))
</taxonomicName>
; in ventral view, paramere distinctly constricted at middle, this point about 0.36 times as broad as median lobe of aedeagus. 
<taxonomicName authority="Fei &amp; Zhou" authorityName="Fei &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2021" box="[835,1259,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eccoptolonthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuyuensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[835,1120,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Eccoptolonthus fuyuensis</emphasis>
Fei &amp; Zhou
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1267,1356,1303,1329]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1267,1356,1303,1329]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sharp, 1874)" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[441,881,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eccoptolonthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gastralis">
<emphasis box="[441,720,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Eccoptolonthus gastralis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sharp, D." box="[735,873,1339,1365]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" pagination="47 - 48" refId="ref16531" refString="Sharp, D. (1874) The Staphylinidae of Japan. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1, 47 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1874. tb 00159. x" type="journal article" year="1874">Sharp, 1874</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: male sternite VIII of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fei &amp; Zhou" authorityName="Fei &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,580,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eccoptolonthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuyuensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,438,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Eccoptolonthus fuyuensis</emphasis>
Fei &amp; Zhou
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[589,680,1375,1401]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[589,680,1375,1401]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
with a pair of long appendages, (
<taxonomicName authority="(Sharp, 1874)" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1874" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eccoptolonthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gastralis">
<emphasis box="[1065,1346,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Eccoptolonthus gastralis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sharp, D." pageId="14" pageNumber="487" pagination="47 - 48" refId="ref16531" refString="Sharp, D. (1874) The Staphylinidae of Japan. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1, 47 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1874. tb 00159. x" type="journal article" year="1874">Sharp, 1874</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
without); in ventral view, paramere distinctly constricted at middle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="487" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,1545]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1447,1473]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the name of the 
<typeStatus box="[845,893,1447,1473]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">type</typeStatus>
locality, Fuyu Mountain (Tianmu Mountain was named as Fuyu Mountain in ancient times).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1032,1518,1545]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,1545]" box="[199,1032,1518,1545]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1518,1544]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is at present known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[887,935,1519,1545]" pageId="14" pageNumber="487">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
